dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.enterprise.wf.wspec.WorkSpecFulfillmentRate
dataStructure.description:
Entity that is used in Planning and WorkSpecification configuration. Represents a rate that shows how many particular work tasks (quantity attribute) can be performed by a given organization in a given location (or serving areas) with a given capacity (Consumption Capacity attribute). For example, with 100 man hours of Fiber layout skills, 200 works of Dig a trench for Underground Cable, 200m length can be performed in an urban area by an organization.

This entity is optional
dataStructure.label: WorkSpecFulfillmentRate

child.name: quantity
child.description:
Maximal number of identical work tasks (defined by WorkSpecification) that the organization can do for the location, using the available capacity, at the same time

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: quantity

child.name: consumptionCapacity
child.description:
Workforce capacity that is required by the work to be done for the location, and that the organization can supply. Unit of the value can be man hour, man day, etc

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: consumptionCapacity

child.name: standardDrivingTime
child.description:
Standard driving time for the organization technicians to drive to and between work places in the serving area

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: standardDrivingTime
